diet, was particularly insightful on the topic of how companies like ChatGP=
T or Perplexity AI, a =E2=80=9Cconversational search engine,=E2=80=9D don=
=E2=80=99t just pose a threat to Google=E2=80=94they present an entirely ne=
w paradigm to engage with news media, too. Here=E2=80=99s Troy, lightly edi=
ted, on why he=E2=80=99s excited about the technology=E2=80=A6<br/><br/><em=
>Troy Young: </em>To me, there are three core modalities that we need to th=
ink about: One is search, which is still going to be around for a long time=
 and is the navigational backbone
of the internet; then there are feeds and the live stuff that gets pushed a=
t you and is curated in some shape or form by an algorithm or editor; and t=
he new one is ChatGPT, where you go ask questions and interrogate things. C=
hatGPT is a little like search, an old process of informing yourself throug=
h the news, because you can interrogate any subject in ChatGPT. Then there =
is Perplexity, which wants to be a news feed because there=E2=80=99s a lot =
of money and value in that. What that amounts to is the
second tab in Perplexity, which has essentially pre-formatted queries that =
turn chat into a feed of things that are the news of the day.=C2=A0<br/><br=
/>Right now, we=E2=80=99re seeing a lot of people fight to build news aggre=
gators that somehow will be the thing you go to every day to get your news.=
 OpenAI doesn=E2=80=99t do news yet, but it=E2=80=99s not inconceivable tha=
t they=E2=80=99re going to start to be proactive, because they know a lot. =
They can query the system according to who you are and they can create a fe=
ed for
you. So this line between what is chat and what is a feed is really interes=
ting.=C2=A0<br/><br/>For example, I=E2=80=99ve been on a little bit of a ra=
bbit hole around <strong>Bob Dylan</strong> lately. I saw the movie on Satu=
rday, and when I was in the car on the way home, I decided to open up ChatG=
PT and sort of interrogate a bunch of Bob Dylan songs with the chat. I went=
 through <em>Like A Rolling Stone</em>, and asked Chat to deconstruct all s=
ix verses, go through line by line, talk about the
brilliance of each of the lines and what Dylan meant by his words, and what=
